# cargo-fuzz outputs.
#
# `corpus/` is intentionally NOT ignored — the seed inputs checked in
# under each target's directory are part of the fuzz harness and must
# travel with the repository so CI runs against them. Newly synthesised
# inputs grow the corpus over time; periodically minimise with
# `cargo fuzz cmin <target>` and commit the reduced set if the corpus
# has grown unwieldy.
target/
artifacts/
coverage/

# fuzz/Cargo.lock IS committed (unlike most cargo-fuzz setups, where it's
# typically gitignored). Reason: this fuzz crate is its own workspace
# (`[workspace]` in Cargo.toml), so cargo resolves its deps independently
# of the parent's Cargo.lock. Without a committed lockfile, CI can pick
# slightly mismatched versions of the tauri-codegen-emitted code vs the
# tauri runtime crate, producing E0063 "missing field" errors at build.
# Committing the lockfile pins both halves to the same version.
